    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-07-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <head>No. 289.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hamlin</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-07-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 10, 1882</date>.
                            (Received July 27, 1882.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 62.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your instruction No. 49, and to
                        my dispatch No. 38, relating to the duty imposed on live fish imported into
                        the Island of Cuba in foreign bottoms, I have now the honor to inclose
                        herewith, for your further information, a copy and translation of a note,
                        dated the 3d instant, upon the subject from the minister of state, by which
                        it will be observed that the subject has been referred to the
                        governor-general for report, which, when received, will be transmitted to
                        the legation.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HANNIBAL HAMLIN.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No.
                            62.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <persName type="from">Marquis de la Vega de
                                    Armijo</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Hamlin</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ministry of
                                    State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName type="venue">
                                <hi rend="italic">Palace</hi>
                            </placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-07-03">
                                <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 3, 1882</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: In answer to the note of your
                            excellency of 27th April ultimo, in which you asked for the suppression
                            of the duty paid on live fish on its importation in foreign bottoms into
                            the Island of Cuba, I have the honor to state that the ministry of
                            ultramar, in view of difficulties encountered, to bring about said
                            suppression, transmitted an “expediente” to the council of state, which
                            has rendered its opinion, in which said ministry has concurred, and in
                            consequence of which said “expediente” has been sent to the
                            governor-general of said island in order that the direction-general of
                            hacienda may report in regard thereto.</p>
                    <p>So soon as this ministry shall be informed of the decision taken, I will
                            hasten to transmit it to your excellency.</p>
                    <p>Availing myself, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>El Marques DE LA VEGA DE ARMIJO.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
